Third-party software, ideas, and patterns this project draws from
================================================================

Vito  (https://github.com/vitodeploy/vito)
  License: AGPL-3.0
  Used as a reference for server provisioning patterns, SSH executor
  design, Let's Encrypt issuance flow, and supervisor/daemon management.
  Aegis is an independent implementation in Go with a different
  architectural foundation (per-site Linux user isolation, native agent,
  containerized Docker site type). No Vito code is copied verbatim;
  patterns and naming conventions are credited here.

satnaing/shadcn-admin  (https://github.com/satnaing/shadcn-admin)
  License: MIT
  Used as the initial scaffold for the React + Vite + shadcn/ui frontend.
  Aegis modifies, removes, and extends this template substantially. The
  original MIT license is retained in web/THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md.

shadcn/ui  (https://ui.shadcn.com/)
  License: MIT
  UI component primitives.

